WorkItem.Description:
I'm using Typescript with the "--out" option.   This concatenates all my generated JS files into a single file taking dependencies into account.  However, I have to concatenate my external Javascript libraries, like JQuery, as an additional step to get them into the monolithic file.

I want to extend "reference" to support Javascript files.  If "--out" is specified, references would be tracked as dependencies and would get copied "as-is" into the monolithic Javascript file.  If "--out" wasn't specified, they would be ignored.

/// <reference path='jquery.js'/>
